946a0e8a-b9fa-4d28-ad9a-de744b57e099.description=Loops over a specified amount of time and averages a value fed into it over this time. Checks to see if this value is above or below a specified threshold. This flow should only be used as a subflow since using it on its own will always return the continue response unless runLength is assigned a value of 0. When this flow gives the continue response the calling flow must obtain another value, and pass it to this flow again. Inputs\: runLength - The number of seconds this flow should loop. waitTime - The number of seconds this flow should before returning when looping. threshold - A value to compare the averaged value to. VALUE - The value of the most recent function call, which will be added to the average. list - The list of values that will be used for finding the average. timeStarted - Time at which the flow is started. Responses\: less than - The average was less than the threshold. equal - the average was the same as the threshold. greater than - the average was greater than the threshold. Continue - the specified amount of time has not yet passed, the calling flow should run another operation and pass this flow another value. failure - values in keyName could not be averaged. Extra results\: average - the average value of the list. only a result is the response is success. list - a list that is accumulating values. This is erased when the time runs out. timeStarted - the time since you made the first function call. this is erased when time runs out.
